@Reasoning:
Public flag accessor: returns the has_error sentinel set by
set_solidity_semantic_error. Distinct from the per-error List
accessors because callers often want a single boolean "did the
analyzer fail fatally" check without iterating the lists.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-guards analyzer. Reads has_error @200 (1 = error, 0 = clean)
and returns the value directly.
@End Implementation
Process called "solidity_semantic_has_errors" takes analyzer as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check if semantic analysis found any errors

    If analyzer is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let errors be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with analyzer, 160
    Let error_count be proc size from List with errors
    Return error_count
End Process